At this stage, it’s still unclear whether this was a gang-related shooting. CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating the fatal shooting of a man in Ocean View, Cape Town. The incident took place in the early hours of Saturday morning. At this stage, it’s still unclear whether this was a gang-related shooting. Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Andre Traut says, “At approximately 6am, a 30-year-old man was shot and killed in Ocean View. The circumstances are being investigated, and no one has been arrested yet.” (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)